main event: Two objects were sighted over Condon AFS, Oregon on March 21, 1966.
interesting points: The objects were described as being the size of a pinhead.
The objects moved at excessive speeds, ranging from 20 knots to 82 knots.
The objects were observed through binoculars and were seen moving at a 35 degree angle.
The sighting lasted for 1 minute and 30 seconds.
The objects faded out to the northeast.
result: The objects were believed to be the ECHO II satellite.
